It’s understood a security guard had been collecting money from a service station this afternoon when he was confronted by two armed men who took cash and his firearm. JOHANNESBURG - Police say a suspected robber has been shot dead in a cash in transit heist in Florida. It’s understood a security guard had been collecting money from a service station this afternoon when he was confronted by two armed men who took cash and his firearm. One of the criminals then shot a tyre of the vehicle while making a getaway. However, their getaway car was spotted by metro police and there was a shootout. One criminal was shot dead while his three accomplices fled the scene, leaving behind an AK 47 rifle and three pistols.